pageContext.claim: “We are advertising all over the place, but as much as we do, the Fake News likes to say we aren't. Just being smart. We have much more money than we had at same time in 2016. Also spending on other, and different, elements of the campaign. Starting to get great poll numbers!”
pageContext.analysis: Reporters accurately noted that the Trump campaign canceled several flights of TV ads heading into the final months of the race. Trump was strapped for cash, while Joe Biden was raking in money from donors and outspending him on television.
